{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859526316,"sessionID":"ses_286863106ffeo6VSneMB4AUo03","part":{"id":"prt_d7979e6cd001Z6RBHS66u6W0Hx","messageID":"msg_d7979dcf4001q7Sh8MFhX29HeX","sessionID":"ses_286863106ffeo6VSneMB4AUo03","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e9deb1e41e9140ad8016b9e1aa9ea463","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: **Feature:** AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n4: **Goal:** Implement Kubernetes-native reconciler controllers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs using controller-runtime to provide automated lifecycle management for sandbox resources with proper event handling and status reporting.\n5: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n6: - AgentRuntimeReconciler successfully creates and manages sandbox resources\n7: - CodeInterpreterReconciler successfully creates and manages sandbox resources\n8: - Status conditions are accurately updated during reconciliation (Ready, Error, Progressing, etc.)\n9: - Finalizers are properly handled for resource deletion\n10: - Events are recorded for all significant operations\n11: - Metrics are exposed and can be scraped by Prometheus\n12: - Unit tests cover all major code paths\n13: - Integration tests validate end-to-end reconciliation\n14: - Error handling is robust and provides clear feedback\n15: - Reconciler can handle spec changes gracefully\n16: - Leader election works correctly in HA deployments\n17: **Architecture:** Controller-runtime based reconciler pattern with separate reconcilers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs, coexisting with existing HTTP-based controller, using agent-sandbox API for sandbox lifecycle management.\n18: **Tech Stack:** Go, controller-runtime, client-go, agent-sandbox API, Prometheus metrics, Ginkgo/Gomega testing\n19: **前端验证:** No\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ### Task 1: Create reconciler package directory structure\n24: \n25: **Files:**\n26: - Create: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/`\n27: \n28: **Step 1: Create reconciler directory**\n29: \n30: ```bash\n31: mkdir -p pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler\n32: ```\n33: \n34: **Step 2: Verify directory created**\n35: \n36: Run: `ls -la pkg/workloadmanager/controller/`\n37: Expected: Output shows reconciler/ directory\n38: \n39: **Step 3: Create package documentation file**\n40: \n41: ```go\n42: // Package reconciler implements Kubernetes reconciler controllers for\n43: // AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs using controller-runtime.\n44: //\n45: // The reconcilers watch for changes to CRDs and automatically manage\n46: // the lifecycle of associated sandbox resources.\n47: package reconciler\n48: ```\n49: \n50: **Step 4: Commit**\n51: \n52: ```bash\n53: git add pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/doc.go\n54: git commit -m \"feat(ar-007): create reconciler package structure\"\n55: ```\n56: \n57: ### Task 2: Define reconciler types and interfaces\n58: \n59: **Files:**\n60: - Create: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/types.go`\n61: \n62: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n63: \n64: ```go\n65: // pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/types_test.go\n66: package reconciler\n67: \n68: import (\n69: \t\"testing\"\n70: \n71: \t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n72: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n73: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/types\"\n74: \tctrl \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n75: )\n76: \n77: func TestReconcilerInterface(t *testing.T) {\n78: \tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n79: \n80: \tvar _ Reconciler = (*AgentRuntimeReconciler)(nil)\n81: \tvar _ Reconciler = (*CodeInterpreterReconciler)(nil)\n82: \tg.Expect(true).To(BeTrue())\n83: }\n84: \n85: func TestControllerConfig(t *testing.T) {\n86: \tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n87: \n88: \tcfg := &ControllerConfig{\n89: \t\tRequeueAfter:          10 * time.Second,\n90: \t\tMaxConcurrentReconciles: 2,\n91: \t}\n92: \n93: \tg.Expect(cfg.RequeueAfter).To(Equal(10 * time.Second))\n94: \tg.Expect(cfg.MaxConcurrentReconciles).To(Equal(2))\n95: }\n96: ```\n97: \n98: **Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n99: \n100: Run: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestReconcilerInterface -v`\n101: Expected: FAIL with \"undefined: Reconciler\" and \"undefined: AgentRuntimeReconciler\"\n102: \n103: **Step 3: Write minimal implementation**\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: package reconciler\n107: \n108: import (\n109: \t\"time\"\n110: \n111: \t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n112: )\n113: \n114: // Reconciler defines the interface for all reconcilers\n115: type Reconciler interface {\n116: \tReconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n117: \tSetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error\n118: }\n119: \n120: // ControllerConfig provides configuration for reconcilers\n121: type ControllerConfig struct {\n122: \t// RequeueAfter is the default requeue interval\n123: \tRequeueAfter time.Duration\n124: \n125: \t// MaxConcurrentReconciles is the maximum number of concurrent reconciles\n126: \tMaxConcurrentReconciles int\n127: \n128: \t// SyncPeriod is the full resync period\n129: \tSyncPeriod *time.Duration\n130: \n131: \t// EnableLeaderElection enables leader election\n132: \tEnableLeaderElection bool\n133: \n134: \t// LeaderElectionID is the leader election ID\n135: \tLeaderElectionID string\n136: \n137: \t// LeaderElectionNamespace is the namespace for leader election\n138: \tLeaderElectionNamespace string\n139: \n140: \t// MetricsAddr is the metrics server address\n141: \tMetricsAddr string\n142: \n143: \t// EnableProfiling enables profiling endpoints\n144: \tEnableProfiling bool\n145: \n146: \t// ProbeAddr is the health probe address\n147: \tProbeAddr string\n148: }\n149: \n150: // AgentRuntimeReconciler reconciles AgentRuntime resources\n151: type AgentRuntimeReconciler struct {\n152: \t// Implementation to be added in subsequent tasks\n153: }\n154: \n155: // CodeInterpreterReconciler reconciles CodeInterpreter resources\n156: type CodeInterpreterReconciler struct {\n157: \t// Implementation to be added in subsequent tasks\n158: }\n159: ```\n160: \n161: **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n162: \n163: Run: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/ -run TestReconcilerInterface -v`\n164: Expected: PASS\n165: \n166: **Step 5: Commit**\n167: \n168: ```bash\n169: git add pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/types.go pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/types_test.go\n170: git commit -m \"feat(ar-007): define reconciler types and interfaces\"\n171: ```\n172: \n173: ### Task 3: Define status condition types and constants\n174: \n175: **Files:**\n176: - Create: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status.go`\n177: \n178: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n179: \n180: ```go\n181: // pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status_test.go\n182: package reconciler\n183: \n184: import (\n185: \t\"testing\"\n186: \n187: \t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n188: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n189: )\n190: \n191: func TestConditionTypes(t *testing.T) {\n192: \tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n193: \n194: \tg.Expect(ConditionTypeReady).To(Equal(\"Ready\"))\n195: \tg.Expect(ConditionTypeAvailable).To(Equal(\"Available\"))\n196: \tg.Expect(ConditionTypeProgressing).To(Equal(\"Progressing\"))\n197: \tg.Expect(ConditionTypeError).To(Equal(\"Error\"))\n198: \tg.Expect(ConditionTypeSandboxCreated).To(Equal(\"SandboxCreated\"))\n199: }\n200: \n201: func TestReasonConstants(t *testing.T) {\n202: \tg := NewGomegaWithT(t)\n203: \n204: \tg.Expect(ReasonReconciliationStarted).To(Equal(\"ReconciliationStarted\"))\n205: \tg.Expect(ReasonSandboxCreated).To(Equal(\"SandboxCreated\"))\n206: \tg.Expect(ReasonValidationFailed).To(Equal(\"ValidationFailed\"))\n207: }\n208: ```\n209: \n210